cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on anaphora resolution, which is a common problem in computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new architecture that involves memory operations, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the use of differentiable gates for training the model could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on a dataset of pronoun-name anaphora, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision), as this type of anaphora resolution is often used in image captioning tasks.
